One of the ways in which we can help prevent conflicts is to strengthen the democratic institutions in the newly independent countries of the former Soviet Union. Respect for the sovereignty of the newly independent countries must remain paramount. The west is sometimes suspicious of Moscow's attitude. They argue that they have a legitimate concern in trying to resolve conflicts that threaten their security. The international community is starting to look beyond the conflict in the former Yugoslavia, and is becoming increasingly aware of the true magnitude and seriousness of ethnic and political conflicts in the former Soviet Union. 